{"word":"σκιατροφέω","slug":"σκιατροφέω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>σκιατροφέω</b></el> <el>(σκιᾱτροφέω,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:τρέφω'><el>τρέφω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to rear in the shade</i>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to keep in the shade, shun heat and labour</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:intransitive'>intr.</a> in <a href='S:active signification'><a href='S:Active voice'>Act.</a></a> <i>to wear a shade, cover one's head</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>; <el>ἐσκιατροφηκώς</el>, of an <i>effeminate</i> man, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}